  "description": "<a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p741108/\"><img src=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/2009/images/rss_shuangyu.gif\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a><br /><p>\n\t<img src=\"http://i2.w.hjfile.cn/doc/201507/a0fd2fbf291b4fd688cb9f965b205eee.jpg\" style=\"height: 330px; width: 440px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n\t&ldquo;If Gared said it was the cold?&rdquo; Will began.<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&ldquo;既然盖瑞都说是天气的关系了&hellip;&hellip;&rdquo;威尔正要开口。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;&ldquo;Have you drawn any watches this past week, Will?&rdquo;<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;&ldquo;威尔，上周你有没有站岗？&rdquo;</span></p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;&ldquo;Yes, my lord.&rdquo; There <strong>never</strong> was a week when he did not draw a dozen bloody watches. What was the man <strong>driving at</strong>?<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;&ldquo;有啊，大人。&rdquo;他哪星期没抽到站岗的签，这家伙究竟想说什么？</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\n\t<img src=\"http://i2.w.hjfile.cn/doc/201507/116e1003b1a84c0e89115fc831a67ee2.gif\" style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\" /><strong>never</strong>在这里提到了be动词之前，更加地强调，没有例外。</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\n\t<img src=\"http://i2.w.hjfile.cn/doc/201507/116e1003b1a84c0e89115fc831a67ee2.gif\" style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\" /><strong>drive at</strong>指一方没有明说或者没有说，而另一方懂得他的意思。即暗示。</p>\n<p>\n\te.g.: It was clear that John didn&rsquo;t understand what Tom was driving at.</p>\n<p>\n\t要是搞不懂别人老在暗示I can&rsquo;t guess what you&rsquo;re driving at.你对我有啥意思没有？</p>\n<p>\n\t暗示还有其他的一些表达，我们来对比一下:</p>\n<p>\n\tShould I drop a hint to Matt? 这里drop a hint 表示透露一点，放口风。动词词组，表隐含的是名词，hint。</p>\n<p>\n\tMr. Thomas has indicated that he may resign. 这里的indicate意指不直白表达，拐外抹角地说。</p>\n<p>\n\tWhat did she imply in her words? 这里imply是暗含，暗语。</p>\n<p>\n\t后两个是动词表隐含。drive at 是固定动词搭配。</p>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;&ldquo;And how did you find the Wall?&rdquo;<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;&ldquo;长城的情形如何？&rdquo;</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&ldquo;</span><strong style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">Weeping,</strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&rdquo; Will said, </span><strong style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">frowning</strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">. He saw it clear enough, now that the lordling had pointed it out. &ldquo;They couldn&rsquo;t have froze. Not if the Wall was weeping. It wasn&rsquo;t cold enough.&rdquo;</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;&ldquo;在&lsquo;哭泣&rsquo;啊，&rdquo;威尔皱着眉头说。这下他明白了。&ldquo;所以他们不是冻死的，假如城墙会滴水，表示天气还不够冷。&rdquo;</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\n\t<img src=\"http://i2.w.hjfile.cn/doc/201507/116e1003b1a84c0e89115fc831a67ee2.gif\" style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\" /><strong>weep</strong>，渗出液体。流出眼泪。</p>\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">\n\t<img src=\"http://i2.w.hjfile.cn/doc/201507/116e1003b1a84c0e89115fc831a67ee2.gif\" style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\" /><strong>frown</strong>，眉头紧皱。</p>\n<p>\n\t此处weeping & frowning 虽然两个词都是v-ing 形式，但前者是动名词而后者则是动词的现在分词。动名词顾名思义是名词，只是由动作演化过来的。而动词分词则是动词的变化形式，或者带有形容词性质表示人或事物的状态。</p>\n<br /><center><a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p741108/#relate_articles\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_chat.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p741108\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_digg.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a></center><h3 style=\"margin: 10px;\">本周最热文章</h3><ul style=\"margin: 5px 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p740532/\">外国人说：妈妈老婆同时掉水里 先救谁？</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p740868/\">跟中国好声音4学英文 Lemon Tree</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p740158/\">外媒看中国：华为科技引爆全球热卖</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p740155/\">哪位女星脚最美？TOP10排名 艾玛沃特森夺冠</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p739908/\">Quora精选：出行他国时的绝对禁忌</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"htt